User-provided URLs are extremely dangerous and can lead to Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) attacks. The Capital One breach in 2019 resulted from exactly this vulnerability - attackers accessed internal AWS metadata services to steal credentials.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

