**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Attacker can reach internal services behind the firewall (Redis, Elasticsearch, internal APIs)
- Cloud metadata endpoints expose IAM credentials, API keys, and instance information
- CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION allows redirect chains to bypass naive URL checks
- No protocol restrictions allow file:// and other dangerous schemes
- Response leakage exposes internal service data directly to attacker

**SECURE VERSION**:

```php
<?php
class SecureWebhookValidator {
    private const ALLOWED_SCHEMES = ['https'];
    private const BLOCKED_HOSTS = [
        'localhost', '127.0.0.1', '0.0.0.0', '::1',
        'metadata.google.internal', 'metadata.goog'
    ];
    private const BLOCKED_IP_RANGES = [
        '10.0.0.0/8',      // Private Class A
        '172.16.0.0/12',   // Private Class B
        '192.168.0.0/16',  // Private Class C
        '169.254.0.0/16',  // Link-local (AWS/cloud metadata)
        '127.0.0.0/8',     // Loopback
        'fc00::/7',        // IPv6 private
        '::1/128'          // IPv6 loopback
    ];

    public function validateWebhook(string $webhookUrl): array {
        // Step 1: Parse and validate URL structure
        $parsedUrl = parse_url($webhookUrl);
        if ($parsedUrl === false || !isset($parsedUrl['host'])) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('Invalid URL format');
        }

        // Step 2: Validate scheme (HTTPS only)
        $scheme = strtolower($parsedUrl['scheme'] ?? '');
        if (!in_array($scheme, self::ALLOWED_SCHEMES, true)) {
            throw new SecurityException('Only HTTPS URLs are allowed');
        }

        // Step 3: Check for blocked hostnames
        $host = strtolower($parsedUrl['host']);
        if (in_array($host, self::BLOCKED_HOSTS, true)) {
            throw new SecurityException('Blocked hostname detected');
        }

        // Step 4: Resolve hostname and validate IP
        $resolvedIps = gethostbynamel($host);
        if ($resolvedIps === false) {
            throw new InvalidArgumentException('Unable to resolve hostname');
        }

        foreach ($resolvedIps as $ip) {
            if ($this->isBlockedIp($ip)) {
                throw new SecurityException('URL resolves to blocked IP range');
            }
        }

        // Step 5: Make request with strict settings
        return $this->makeSecureRequest($webhookUrl, $resolvedIps[0]);
    }

    private function isBlockedIp(string $ip): bool {
        foreach (self::BLOCKED_IP_RANGES as $range) {
            if ($this->ipInRange($ip, $range)) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    private function ipInRange(string $ip, string $cidr): bool {
        list($subnet, $bits) = explode('/', $cidr);
        $ip = ip2long($ip);
        $subnet = ip2long($subnet);
        $mask = -1 << (32 - $bits);
        return ($ip & $mask) === ($subnet & $mask);
    }

    private function makeSecureRequest(string $url, string $resolvedIp): array {
        $ch = curl_init();
        curl_setopt_array($ch, [
            CURLOPT_URL => $url,
            CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
            CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION => false,  // Disable redirects
            CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => 5,
            CURLOPT_CONNECTTIMEOUT => 3,
            CURLOPT_PROTOCOLS => CURLPROTO_HTTPS,  // Only HTTPS
            CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER => true,
            CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST => 2,
            CURLOPT_RESOLVE => [parse_url($url, PHP_URL_HOST) . ':443:' . $resolvedIp]
        ]);

        $response = curl_exec($ch);
        $httpCode = curl_getinfo($ch, CURLINFO_HTTP_CODE);
        $error = curl_error($ch);
        curl_close($ch);

        if ($response === false) {
            throw new RuntimeException('Request failed: ' . $error);
        }

        // Don't return response content - just validation status
        return [
            'valid' => $httpCode >= 200 && $httpCode < 300,
            'status_code' => $httpCode
        ];
    }
}

class SecurityException extends Exception {}
?>
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Scheme whitelist**: Only HTTPS allowed, preventing file://, gopher://, dict:// protocols
- **DNS resolution validation**: Resolves hostname BEFORE request and validates against blocked IP ranges
- **IP range blocking**: Comprehensive list including RFC1918 private ranges and cloud metadata IPs (169.254.x.x)
- **Redirect prevention**: CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION disabled to prevent redirect-based bypasses
- **Response sanitization**: Only returns status code, not response body, preventing data exfiltration

Excellent question! DNS rebinding is a sophisticated attack where the attacker controls a DNS server that initially returns a safe IP, passes your validation, then changes to return an internal IP for the actual request. Combined with redirect chains, this can bypass many SSRF protections.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```php
<?php
declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Security;

use Psr\Log\LoggerInterface;
use Redis;

class ProductionSSRFProtection {
    private const ALLOWED_SCHEMES = ['https'];
    private const MAX_REDIRECTS = 0;
    private const REQUEST_TIMEOUT = 5;
    private const DNS_CACHE_TTL = 300;

    private const BLOCKED_IP_RANGES = [
        '0.0.0.0/8', '10.0.0.0/8', '100.64.0.0/10', '127.0.0.0/8',
        '169.254.0.0/16', '172.16.0.0/12', '192.0.0.0/24',
        '192.0.2.0/24', '192.168.0.0/16', '198.18.0.0/15',
        '198.51.100.0/24', '203.0.113.0/24', '224.0.0.0/4',
        '240.0.0.0/4', '255.255.255.255/32'
    ];

    private const BLOCKED_HOSTNAMES = [
        'localhost', 'metadata.google.internal', 'metadata.goog',
        'kubernetes.default.svc', 'kubernetes.default'
    ];

    private LoggerInterface $logger;
    private Redis $cache;
    private array $allowedDomains;

    public function __construct(
        LoggerInterface $logger,
        Redis $cache,
        array $allowedDomains = []
    ) {
        $this->logger = $logger;
        $this->cache = $cache;
        $this->allowedDomains = $allowedDomains;
    }

    public function validateAndFetch(string $url, string $requestId): array {
        $context = ['request_id' => $requestId, 'url' => $this->sanitizeUrlForLog($url)];

        try {
            // Layer 1: URL structure validation
            $parsedUrl = $this->validateUrlStructure($url);

            // Layer 2: Domain allowlist check (if configured)
            $this->validateDomainAllowlist($parsedUrl['host']);

            // Layer 3: Hostname blocklist check
            $this->validateHostnameBlocklist($parsedUrl['host']);

            // Layer 4: DNS resolution with rebinding protection
            $resolvedIp = $this->resolveWithRebindingProtection($parsedUrl['host']);

            // Layer 5: IP range validation
            $this->validateIpNotBlocked($resolvedIp, $parsedUrl['host']);

            // Layer 6: Make request with IP pinning
            $result = $this->makeSecureRequestWithPinning($url, $parsedUrl, $resolvedIp);

            $this->logger->info('SSRF_VALIDATION_SUCCESS', $context);
            return $result;

        } catch (SSRFSecurityException $e) {
            $context['violation_type'] = $e->getViolationType();
            $context['violation_details'] = $e->getMessage();
            $this->logger->warning('SSRF_VALIDATION_BLOCKED', $context);

            // Alert on potential attack patterns
            $this->checkAndAlertAttackPattern($url, $e->getViolationType());

            throw $e;
        }
    }

    private function validateUrlStructure(string $url): array {
        // Normalize and parse URL
        $url = trim($url);

        // Block URL encoding tricks
        if (preg_match('/%[0-9a-fA-F]{2}/', $url)) {
            $decodedUrl = urldecode($url);
            if ($decodedUrl !== $url) {
                throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                    'URL encoding detected',
                    'url_encoding_bypass'
                );
            }
        }

        $parsed = parse_url($url);
        if ($parsed === false || !isset($parsed['host'], $parsed['scheme'])) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException('Invalid URL structure', 'malformed_url');
        }

        // Validate scheme
        if (!in_array(strtolower($parsed['scheme']), self::ALLOWED_SCHEMES, true)) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Invalid scheme: ' . $parsed['scheme'],
                'blocked_scheme'
            );
        }

        // Block userinfo in URL (http://user@internal-host/)
        if (isset($parsed['user']) || isset($parsed['pass'])) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Credentials in URL not allowed',
                'url_credentials_bypass'
            );
        }

        // Block suspicious port usage
        if (isset($parsed['port']) && !in_array($parsed['port'], [80, 443], true)) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Non-standard port not allowed: ' . $parsed['port'],
                'blocked_port'
            );
        }

        return $parsed;
    }

    private function validateDomainAllowlist(string $host): void {
        if (empty($this->allowedDomains)) {
            return; // Allowlist not configured
        }

        $host = strtolower($host);
        foreach ($this->allowedDomains as $allowedDomain) {
            if ($host === $allowedDomain || 
                str_ends_with($host, '.' . $allowedDomain)) {
                return;
            }
        }

        throw new SSRFSecurityException(
            'Domain not in allowlist: ' . $host,
            'domain_not_allowed'
        );
    }

    private function validateHostnameBlocklist(string $host): void {
        $host = strtolower($host);

        // Check exact matches and patterns
        foreach (self::BLOCKED_HOSTNAMES as $blocked) {
            if ($host === $blocked || str_contains($host, $blocked)) {
                throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                    'Blocked hostname pattern',
                    'blocked_hostname'
                );
            }
        }

        // Check for IP address in hostname (bypass attempt)
        if (filter_var($host, FILTER_VALIDATE_IP)) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Direct IP addresses not allowed',
                'direct_ip_blocked'
            );
        }

        // Check for decimal/octal/hex IP encoding
        if (preg_match('/^[0-9.]+$/', $host) || 
            preg_match('/^0x[0-9a-fA-F]+$/', $host) ||
            preg_match('/^[0-7]+$/', $host)) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Encoded IP address detected',
                'encoded_ip_bypass'
            );
        }
    }

    private function resolveWithRebindingProtection(string $host): string {
        // Check DNS cache first to prevent rebinding
        $cacheKey = 'dns_resolve:' . sha1($host);
        $cachedIp = $this->cache->get($cacheKey);

        if ($cachedIp !== false) {
            return $cachedIp;
        }

        // Resolve DNS multiple times to detect rebinding
        $resolutions = [];
        for ($i = 0; $i < 3; $i++) {
            $ips = gethostbynamel($host);
            if ($ips === false || empty($ips)) {
                throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                    'DNS resolution failed',
                    'dns_resolution_failed'
                );
            }
            $resolutions[] = $ips[0];
            usleep(100000); // 100ms between resolutions
        }

        // Check for DNS rebinding (IP changed between resolutions)
        if (count(array_unique($resolutions)) > 1) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'DNS rebinding attack detected',
                'dns_rebinding_detected'
            );
        }

        $resolvedIp = $resolutions[0];

        // Cache the resolved IP
        $this->cache->setex($cacheKey, self::DNS_CACHE_TTL, $resolvedIp);

        return $resolvedIp;
    }

    private function validateIpNotBlocked(string $ip, string $host): void {
        foreach (self::BLOCKED_IP_RANGES as $range) {
            if ($this->ipInCidr($ip, $range)) {
                throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                    "Host {$host} resolves to blocked IP range",
                    'blocked_ip_range'
                );
            }
        }
    }

    private function ipInCidr(string $ip, string $cidr): bool {
        if (strpos($ip, ':') !== false) {
            return $this->ipv6InCidr($ip, $cidr);
        }

        list($subnet, $bits) = explode('/', $cidr);
        $ip = ip2long($ip);
        $subnet = ip2long($subnet);

        if ($ip === false || $subnet === false) {
            return false;
        }

        $mask = -1 << (32 - (int)$bits);
        return ($ip & $mask) === ($subnet & $mask);
    }

    private function ipv6InCidr(string $ip, string $cidr): bool {
        // IPv6 handling - block all IPv6 for simplicity or implement proper check
        return true; // Block all IPv6 by default
    }

    private function makeSecureRequestWithPinning(
        string $url,
        array $parsedUrl,
        string $pinnedIp
    ): array {
        $ch = curl_init();

        // Pin the resolved IP to prevent TOCTOU race conditions
        $resolveOption = $parsedUrl['host'] . ':443:' . $pinnedIp;

        curl_setopt_array($ch, [
            CURLOPT_URL => $url,
            CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER => true,
            CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION => false,
            CURLOPT_MAXREDIRS => self::MAX_REDIRECTS,
            CURLOPT_TIMEOUT => self::REQUEST_TIMEOUT,
            CURLOPT_CONNECTTIMEOUT => 3,
            CURLOPT_PROTOCOLS => CURLPROTO_HTTPS,
            CURLOPT_REDIR_PROTOCOLS => 0, // No redirect protocols allowed
            CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER => true,
            CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST => 2,
            CURLOPT_RESOLVE => [$resolveOption],
            CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER => [
                'User-Agent: WebhookValidator/1.0',
                'Accept: application/json'
            ],
            // Prevent response from being too large
            CURLOPT_BUFFERSIZE => 8192,
            CURLOPT_NOPROGRESS => false,
            CURLOPT_PROGRESSFUNCTION => function($ch, $dlTotal, $dlNow) {
                // Abort if response exceeds 1MB
                return ($dlNow > 1048576) ? 1 : 0;
            }
        ]);

        $response = curl_exec($ch);
        $httpCode = curl_getinfo($ch, CURLINFO_HTTP_CODE);
        $effectiveUrl = curl_getinfo($ch, CURLINFO_EFFECTIVE_URL);
        $error = curl_error($ch);
        curl_close($ch);

        // Final redirect check (defense in depth)
        if ($effectiveUrl !== $url) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Unexpected redirect detected',
                'redirect_detected'
            );
        }

        if ($response === false) {
            throw new SSRFSecurityException(
                'Request failed: ' . $error,
                'request_failed'
            );
        }

        return [
            'valid' => $httpCode >= 200 && $httpCode < 300,
            'status_code' => $httpCode,
            'pinned_ip' => $pinnedIp
        ];
    }

    private function checkAndAlertAttackPattern(string $url, string $violationType): void {
        $alertTypes = [
            'dns_rebinding_detected',
            'blocked_ip_range',
            'encoded_ip_bypass',
            'url_credentials_bypass'
        ];

        if (in_array($violationType, $alertTypes, true)) {
            // Send to SIEM/alerting system
            $this->logger->critical('SSRF_ATTACK_DETECTED', [
                'violation_type' => $violationType,
                'url_hash' => sha256($url),
                'timestamp' => time()
            ]);
        }
    }

    private function sanitizeUrlForLog(string $url): string {
        // Remove sensitive parts for logging
        $parsed = parse_url($url);
        if ($parsed === false) {
            return '[invalid_url]';
        }
        return ($parsed['scheme'] ?? 'unknown') . '://' . 
               ($parsed['host'] ?? '[no_host]') . 
               ($parsed['path'] ?? '/');
    }
}

class SSRFSecurityException extends \Exception {
    private string $violationType;

    public function __construct(string $message, string $violationType) {
        parent::__construct($message);
        $this->violationType = $violationType;
    }

    public function getViolationType(): string {
        return $this->violationType;
    }
}
?>
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **URL Structure Validation** - Blocks encoded characters, userinfo bypass (http://user@host), and non-standard ports
```php
// Block URL encoding tricks and userinfo bypass
if (preg_match('/%[0-9a-fA-F]{2}/', $url)) {
    throw new SSRFSecurityException('URL encoding detected', 'url_encoding_bypass');
}
if (isset($parsed['user']) || isset($parsed['pass'])) {
    throw new SSRFSecurityException('Credentials in URL not allowed', 'url_credentials_bypass');
}
```

2. **DNS Rebinding Protection** - Multiple DNS resolutions with comparison and caching
```php
// Resolve multiple times to detect rebinding attacks
for ($i = 0; $i < 3; $i++) {
    $resolutions[] = gethostbynamel($host)[0];
    usleep(100000);
}
if (count(array_unique($resolutions)) > 1) {
    throw new SSRFSecurityException('DNS rebinding attack detected', 'dns_rebinding_detected');
}
```

3. **IP Pinning with CURLOPT_RESOLVE** - Ensures the request uses the validated IP
```php
// Pin resolved IP to prevent TOCTOU race conditions
CURLOPT_RESOLVE => [$parsedUrl['host'] . ':443:' . $pinnedIp]
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Domain allowlisting**: For webhook scenarios, only allow known webhook providers (Slack, Discord, etc.)
- **Response size limiting**: CURLOPT_PROGRESSFUNCTION prevents resource exhaustion from large responses
- **Comprehensive IP blocking**: Includes RFC1918, link-local, multicast, and documentation ranges
- **Security alerting**: Distinguishes between user errors and attack patterns for targeted alerts
- **Audit logging**: All validation attempts logged with request ID for correlation
- **IPv6 blocking**: Blocks IPv6 by default to prevent bypass via IPv6-mapped IPv4 addresses
